title: Take Your Little Gun and Get Out of My Trailer Park
description: After an 18-month jail sentence, Ricky and Julian head home to get their lives back together but a bully has taken control of the park.

title: F**k Community College, Let's Get Drunk and Eat Chicken Fingers
description: Julian decides to depart Sunnyvale Trailer Park and go to community college to finally do something productive in his life.

title: Mr. Lahey's Got My Porno Tape!
description: Ricky and Bubbles agree to star in J-Roc's porno film but Ricky loses his nerve, forcing Bubbles to stand in for him on a particularly steamy scene.

title: Mrs. Peterson's Dog Gets F**ked Up
description: Ricky lets a dog devour a tray of hash brownies and takes the dog to the local veterinarian. He must then run errands for the vet to pay for it.

title: I'm Not Gay, I Love Lucy... Wait a Second, Maybe I Am Gay
description: Julian convinces Ricky that it's time to marry Lucy. Reluctant at first, Ricky changes his mind when Julian suggests that people will assume he's gay.

title: Who the Hell Invited These Idiots to My Wedding?
description: Lucy asks Julian to plan the wedding since she thinks Ricky is not up to it, but his plans ruin the wedding when the cops show up.

title: What in the F**k Happened to Our Trailer Park?
description: After nearly six months in jail, Ricky and Julian come back to find the trailer park a disaster. They reveal to Bubbles their plan to start a grow op.

title: Jim Lahey Is a Drunk Bastard
description: Julian and Ricky have to make sure that Jim Lahey wins the election for trailer park supervisor over their archrival Sam Losco, who is also running.

title: I've Met Cats and Dogs Smarter than Trevor and Cory
description: Needing extra cash to expand their dope operation without raising Lahey's suspicions, Julian and Ricky open a disco bar in J-Roc's trailer.

title: A Dope Trailer Is No Place for a Kitty
description: When their dope plants become infested with insects, Ricky and Julian quarantine the surviving crop in Bubbles's shed, leading to a fiery conclusion.

title: The Bible Pimp
description: A couple pretending to be a preacher and his daughter selling Bibles comes to the park, hoping to make off with lots of cash.

title: Never Trust a Man with No Shirt On
description: Randy joins Julian and Ricky in their life of crime. However, when Randy is caught spying on them, it puts their dope operation in danger.

title: The Bare Pimp Project
description: Julian asks J-Roc to make another porno film to make Barb dump Sam, Ricky gets his Grade 10, and Julian successfully sells the hash.

title: The Kiss of Freedom
description: After their release from prison, Ricky and Julian are free and rich, thanks to their huge dope sale to the prison guards and inmates.

title: Temporary Relief Assistant Trailer Park Supervisor
description: Ricky wins the new position of temporary relief assistant trailer park supervisor after Randy is suspended by Barb Lahey.

title: If I Can't Smoke and Swear I'm F**ked
description: Julian reveals a new plan to the boys that involves committing various small crimes so they can't go to jail, and saving the money for a cruise trip.

title: Who's the Microphone Assassin?
description: The boys decide to put on a rap concert in celebration of J-Roc's new CD. Things take a turn for the worse when J-Roc is caught masturbating.

title: Closer to the Heart
description: When ripped off on buying Rush tickets by Lahey and Randy, Ricky "borrows" guitarist Alex Lifeson for tickets. Lifeson's hotel room number is 2112.

title: Where in the F**k Is Randy's Barbeque?
description: Ricky conspires to get rich by using kids to help him steal barbecues, as minors are protected under the Youth Justice Act.

title: The Delusions of Officer Jim Lahey
description: It's the anniversary of Mr. Lahey's being fired from the police force.

title: A Sh*t Leopard Can't Change Its Spots
description: Upon realizing that he has no ticket for the eagerly awaited cruise and being evicted from the trailer park, Ricky is determined to go back to jail.

title: Never Cry Sh*twolf
description: After eight months behind bars, Julian, Mr. Lahey and Randy are released, only to discover that Ricky is the new supervisor of Sunnyvale Trailer Park.

title: A Man's Gotta Eat
description: Broke and tired of Ricky's illegal plans, Julian decides to leave the trailer park to live in his car. Meanwhile, Randy resorts to prostitution.

title: Rub 'N Tiz'zug
description: Ricky and Bubbles mistake Julian for a "Samsquanch" and beat up each other with baseball bats. They also open a massage parlor in the park.

title: The Green Bastard
description: When Ricky plans to have a community day in the park complete with wrestling, Bubbles assumes the identity of a wrestler from "parts unknown."

title: Conky
description: When Bubbles has a toothache, he tries everything to get rid of it. Julian tells him that he must go to the hospital.

title: If You Love Something Set It Free
description: Ricky, Julian and Bubbles find a mountain lion in their marijuana field eating their weed. Things get complicated when Bubbles befriends the animal.

title: Propane, Propane
description: The boys plan to smuggle the dope and sell it at a Snoop Dogg concert. Lahey asks Barb to marry him again, but Barb declines.

title: Working Man
description: The boys hold Rita MacNeil and her entourage hostage and force them to help harvest the dope crop. A hostile standoff ensues.

title: Give Peace a Chance
description: After a brief stint in jail, Ricky, Julian and Bubbles return to the trailer park in style, but soon discover that Trevor and Cory lost their money.

title: The Sh*t Puppets
description: Cory and Trevor go to work for Julian and help him steal hash from Cyrus, Terry and Dennis, then concoct a plan to hide it until they find a buyer.

title: The F**kin Way She Goes
description: Ricky, Julian and Bubbles hide their hash under Ray's driveway. Ray's addictions worsen. Ricky barbecues for his family, with devastating results.

title: You Got to Blame the Thing Up Here
description: Ricky, Julian and Bubbles help Ray find a new home after his trailer burns down in a fire that Ricky caused. However, it's Bubbles who gets the blame.

title: Jim Lahey Is a F**kin' Drunk and He Always Will Be
description: Bubbles pretends to be a spaceman when the boys steal a rocket set. Ray reveals Lahey's secret, and Lahey goes off the deep end.

title: Don't Cross the Sh*t Line
description: Ray and Bubbles star in another of J-Roc's adult films, but Lahey and Randy confiscate J-Roc's tape, which has evidence of Ray's disability fraud.

title: The Winds of Sh*t
description: Ricky tries to go back to school but ends up working as a janitor selling dope to the students. Lahey has disturbing visions of the future.

title: Dressed All Over & Zesty Mordant
description: Julian's biggest moneymaking scheme involves smuggling the hash using the shopping carts at a local mall. Trinity gets charged with underage driving.

title: I Am the Liquor
description: Ricky bails Trinity out of jail. Lahey goes on a bender and tricks Cory and Trevor into giving him information. Julian tries to get his trailer back.

title: Sh*t Blizzard
description: Cyrus and his gang are bailed out of jail by Randy and immediately go after Ricky, Julian and Bubbles for getting them busted and taking their hash.

title: Way of the Road
description: Ray gets booted out of Sunnyvale, Julian sells booze in jail, Randy gets fed up with Lahey's drinking, and Bubbles opens a daycare for cats.

title: The Cheeseburger Picnic
description: While Randy organizes a trailer park-wide cheeseburger picnic, Lahey pretends to be drunk in hopes of catching the boys breaking the law.

title: High Definition Piss Jugs
description: When a local TV station comes to Sunnyvale, Cory and Trevor try to publicize their business, and Bubbles promotes his Kittyland Love Center.

title: Where in the F**k Is Oscar Goldman?
description: Bubbles's kitty daycare gets some actual customers, and Ricky and Julian must track down Trinity's lost chicken to keep her from failing sixth grade.

title: Halloween 1977
description: Randy goes nuts with his eviction policy, and Lahey uncovers evidence that the boys were behind the prank that got him fired from the police force.

title: Gimme My F**king Money or Randy's Dead
description: Blaming Randy for getting him fired, Sam Losco takes him captive and holds him for ransom. Meanwhile, Bubbles helps Lahey get back his badge.

title: I F**kin' Miss Cory & Trevor
description: Ricky and Bubbles try to profit by selling stolen meat from a grocery store. Meanwhile, Lucy is pregnant and more demanding to Ricky.

title: I Banged Lucy and Knocked Her Up, No Big Deal
description: J-Roc organizes a gang to steal bags at the airport. We learn more about Lucy's pregnancy and that Ricky is not actually the father of Lucy's child.

title: Three Good Men Are Dead
description: Officers George Green and Ted Johnston attempt to kill Lahey, Randy and Phil Collins for not filing search warrants against Julian and J-Roc.

title: Friends of the Road
description: At a model train convention hosted by Sebastian Bach, Ray gets busted for soliciting an undercover cop, leaving Bubbles stranded in a phone booth.

title: The Mustard Tiger
description: Julian comes up with a plan to smuggle dope into Maine by using a model train that Bubbles stole.

title: We Can't Call People Without Wings Angels, So We Call Them Friends
description: The boys head to the woods in search of Jacob and his friends and soon come across Julian's 1987 Monte Carlo in the river.

title: Jump the Cheeseburger
description: Randy and Phil Collins are busy with final preparations before the opening of The Dirty Burger, including a bicycle stunt by Randy that goes wrong.

title: Let the Liquor Do the Thinking
description: Randy and Lahey get back together with the help of alcohol. Randy tries to break off his engagement with Lucy. Bubbles is having problems.

title: Going Off the Rails on the Swayzie Train
description: The Boys proceed with their cross-border shipment plan with Sebastian Bach. But can they trust their crew?

title: A Sh*t River Runs Through It
description: This episode revolves around the conclusion of the boys' plan to smuggle dope to the United States. As usual, the plan doesn't go quite to plan.

title: Money Can Suck My C**k
description: The boys each have new moneymaking schemes, Jim Lahey is on the verge of retiring and Randy has a new assistant.

title: The F**kin' V-Team
description: Julian offers to partner with Barb so that she can keep the trailer park, but they need Jim Lahey's cooperation over his deciding one percent share.

title: The Dirty Dancer
description: Julian enlists J-Roc and Sarah's aid to turn his bar into a strip club. Ricky is not pleased when he finds out that his daughter Trinity is pregnant.

title: Orangie's Pretty F**kin' Tough
description: When Orangie, Ricky's goldfish, dies after being given too many shooters, Julian and Bubbles try to replace it with another before Ricky finds out.

title: Whore-A-Geddon
description: TV celebrity Steve Rogers rents Julian's bar for his stag party, which gets of out hand and overflows into Bubbles's Shed-and-Breakfast sheds.

title: Friends with the Benedicts
description: Bubbles's attempts to clear up a crab infestation in his sheds and on his kitties cause him embarrassment, and he's arrested for indecent exposure.

title: Community Service and a Boner Made with Love
description: Sentenced to community service, Bubbles insists that Julian and Ricky help him with a school puppet show. The Green Bastard teaches Ricky a lesson.

title: The Super-Duper-Industrial-Bubbles-Honey-Oil-Inator
description: When the compressor air conditioner breaks, Bubbles has to turn his sheds into an industrial honey oil manufacturing complex to save Ricky's weed.

title: Righties Loosies, Lefties Tighties
description: While being filmed by George Green, Bubbles gets his oil production going, aiming to make enough money to buy the trailer park for Barb and Julian.

title: Crawling Through the Sh*tpipe
description: The boys sell their entire honey oil output to Sebastian Bach, but to seal the deal for the trailer park, Julian has to do something truly terrible.

title: Why in the F**k Is My Trailer Pink?
description: Julian and Ricky get out of jail and return to the Sunnyvale Trailer Park, but when they arrive, they find that nothing is as they left it.

title: A Stable F**king Environment
description: Ricky tries to keep his family together despite not being allowed back in the park, while Julian and Bubbles try to get business going again.

title: Anointed In Liquor
description: Julian hatches a plan to secure a place to live while Ricky and his family struggle with their new life in the barn.

title: George Green: Industrial C**k Inhaler
description: Julian and his crew have a motel auction while Ricky must track down a list full of baby items to keep his family together.

title: The Motel Can't Live at the Motel
description: Ricky brings his grandson home to the motel, but it doesn't go as planned, and Julian implements the first stage in his bid to get Sunnyvale back.

title: Sweet Liquory Load
description: J-Roc struggles with his new role as a father, and Julian's plan to get the park back earns Ricky a piece of Leslie's wrath.

title: Piss
description: Mr. Lahey falls off the wagon on the day of Sunnyvale's big appraisal, which Julian, Ricky and the crew do their best to ruin.

title: A Dancer for Money
description: Leslie puts Sunnyvale Park under lock-down, Ricky holds an open house at the motel, and Ricky also has an adventure in the woods.

title: Sam-Squamptches and Heli-C**ksuckers
description: Julian gets desperate in his attempt to reclaim Sunnyvale, Ricky finally might get his family back, and Mr. Lahey falls further off the wagon.

title: The Liquor Snurf
description: It's morning in Sunnyvale as Julian carries out the final stage of his big reverse psychology plan to get his beloved trailer park back.

title: Freedom 45?
description: While Julian celebrates the bar's success and Ricky and Lucy try for a baby, a familiar face returns from jail to shake things up at the park.

title: You Want the Lot Fees, Suck Them Out of the Tip of My C**k
description: Desperate for quick cash to fight the court case, the boys try to collect outstanding lot fees at the park and consider a return to petty crime.

title: A Three Tiered Sh*t Dyke
description: As Barb and her sidekicks try to strong-arm Lahey and Randy into testifying for her in court, the boys set out to case a fancy neighborhood.

title: Sh*t Covered Cave Teeth
description: After handing over Trinity's wedding money, Ricky swears off crime, but Julian tries to talk him into one last job at the Denture King offices.

title: If You Don't Believe It, It's Not Real
description: When a truck heist goes awry, the boys turn to Sam the Denture King for help. But a fight at his office quickly spirals out of control.

title: All the F**kin' Dope You Can Smoke!
description: When Julian turns his bar into an all-inclusive casino, the ad made by Bubbles and Ricky stirs up trouble and gets a celebrity's attention.

title: Up In Smoke We Go
description: A visit from Snoop Dogg and friends sets the trailer park abuzz, and Sunnyvale fan Tom Arnold fulfills a bucket-list dream with Bubbles.

title: The Super Bling Cowboy
description: Bubbles battles a bad case of nerves at his open mic gig, and Lucy weighs a startling offer from Tom Arnold.

title: Thugged Out Gangsta Sh*t
description: Tom sets out on an adventure with Lucy, while Snoop tries Ricky's new concoction and Lahey plots a diabolical mission.

title: Looks Like the Liquor Wins
description: Still shaken up, the gang gets ready for Trinity and Jacob's wedding. Meanwhile, Barb struggles with a big decision about the park.

title: The Jack Your C**k Furry Whore Slut
description: Bubbles and Ricky are doing well with their new pizza sauce company, but a new opportunity arises when they get a tip on where Julian's been living.

title: The Walker Zombley
description: Ricky mistakes a sick-looking Jacob for a "zombley," while Bubs thinks he's an alien. The boys make Cory and Jacob steal fertilizer from a farmer.

title: My F**king Balls, My C**k, My Hole, or My T*ts?
description: When Ricky gets shot in the groin by Mo, the boys argue over what kind of medical attention -- if any -- he should receive.

title: Darth Lahey
description: Ricky has to stay behind and look after Mo while Julian and Bubbles go lobster fishing. Lahey warns Ricky that the cops are out to get them.

title: Flight of the Bumblecock
description: Ricky has a meltdown trying to process information he learned from Lahey. The boys have to get Bubbles's truck back from George Green.

title: How Do You Keep Your Bag So Soft?
description: Ricky's injury isn't healing properly, so the boys head back to see Sam Losco. Ricky takes drastic action when the power gets shut off at the rink.

title: I Look Like A F**KING DICK!!
description: Julian sends Lahey and Ricky off on a golf outing, leading to a confrontation. NHL star Nathan MacKinnon visits the hockey school kids.

title: A Liquor Captain Never Abandons a Sinking Sh*t Ship
description: A "free weed" sign draws a bunch of stoners to the shipping container, where the boys face off with Lahey, Randy and a pair of cops.

title: Oh, My F**k Boys, We Killed Lahey & Randy
description: The boys' deal with Snoop Dogg hits a snag when they're accused of killing Lahey and Randy, then everything goes haywire with Cory and Jacob.

title: The All You Can Eat Sh*t Buffet
description: All hell breaks loose on the ocean as the boys prepare for the drop-off while trying to find Bubbles and avoid Lahey and Randy.

title: Chlamydia
description: Bubbles's new brewing business is taking off, but things aren't going well for Julian and even worse for Ricky, who claims he has a big announcement.

title: Godspeed My Muscular Friend
description: In an attempt to go legit, Julian looks for a job at the mall and Ricky becomes a handyman. Lahey and Randy head to the racetrack.

title: The C**t Word
description: Julian runs a side hustle at his security job. Ricky sends Jacob and Trinity to his car when he hosts Susan for a romantic dinner that turns chaotic.

title: All The Sh*t I Need
description: Bubs loses it when Ricky "borrows" the truck to deal with a rat problem in the park, then lends it to Julian as part of another racket at the mall.

title: Happy Birthday Bubbles
description: The boys cause a panic in the trailer park when a stunt they organize for Bubbles's birthday goes a bit haywire. Julian puts his job in jeopardy.

title: Flow Me The Money
description: The Boys learn that the prosecutor for Julian's trial is his ex. Ricky steps in to represent Julian in court after another plan goes awry.

title: Big C**k
description: Ricky and Julian help Bubbles fill a huge order of his new beer, Freedom 35, but a secret Ricky's been keeping could derail the delivery.

title: Will You For To Be F**king Married To Me?
description: Lahey tries to squeeze his way into the beer business. Ricky and Susan's fighting prevents Candy from getting a private moment with Julian.

title: Angel Sh*t Sent Down From Jesus God
description: When a big beer company wants to work with the Boys, they need to come up with $50,000 to close the deal -- and Ricky has an idea that could pay off.

title: F**kin’ F**ked Out Of Our F**kin’ Minds
description: Bubbles organizes a huge stag party for Julian and Ricky, but when they hear police sirens approaching, it turns into an escape operation.
